docs.abstract: In new tests, Amazon’s system had more difficulty identifying the gender of female and darker-skinned faces than similar services from IBM and Microsoft.
docs.snippet: In new tests, Amazon’s system had more difficulty identifying the gender of female and darker-skinned faces than similar services from IBM and Microsoft.
docs.lead_paragraph: Over the last two years, Amazon has aggressively marketed its facial recognition technology to police departments and federal agencies as a service to help law enforcement identify suspects more quickly. It has done so as another tech giant, Microsoft, has called on Congress to regulate the technology, arguing that it is too risky for companies to oversee on their own.

headline.main: Amazon Is Pushing Facial Technology That a Study Says Could Be Biased

docs.abstract: Accessories and data may not take up much physical space, but they contribute to frustration and anxiety. Here are ways to keep e-junk at bay, Marie Kondo-style.

docs.lead_paragraph: With a new year and a new Netflix show that features the Japanese organizing guru Marie Kondo on the art of “Tidying Up,” many of us are experimenting with how to simplify our lives by purging our homes of unwanted possessions.

headline.main: How to Declutter and Organize Your Personal Tech in a Few Simple Steps
headline.print_headline: A Digital Spree, Then the Purge

docs.abstract: Prosecutors in Japan can detain defendants for weeks before bringing charges, arrest them time and again, and interrogate them without their lawyers.
docs.snippet: Prosecutors in Japan can detain defendants for weeks before bringing charges, arrest them time and again, and interrogate them without their lawyers.
docs.lead_paragraph: TOKYO — After Bernard L. Madoff, arguably the most notorious financial criminal of all time, was arrested for defrauding investors in a multibillion-dollar Ponzi scheme, he was released on $10 million in bail the same day. Until his trial months later, he lived and slept  in his Manhattan penthouse.

headline.main: Carlos Ghosn Declares His Innocence and Is Denied Bail in Japan. That’s a Pattern.
headline.print_headline: Bail Denied, Ghosn Idles In Tokyo Jail. Like Others.
